appended to the command line argument list, which could make two

different VTSs effectively have same set of args.

command line arguments.

a performance issue though. The 'in' operation on the list takes about

entry.content:

line for an `NGInlineNode`. This class is a preparation to

Currently, this class supports:

* Up to single exclusion.

font, without non-initial `vertical-align`.

only from unit tests. It will be used in following patches.

entry.title: media/gpu/v4l2: Drop AV1_PROFILE fallback macros
entry.content:
When the AV1 stateless decoder uAPI was first introduced, the AV1

profile identifiers used the stateless codec namespace. This was later

corrected to use the standard codec namespace. Fallback macros were

added to Chromium to be backward compatible to aid in the uAPI

migration.



The code used the standard codec namespace identifiers from the start

[1], but the fallback macros were never removed after the uAPI was

updated. They still worked because on the uAPI side, another set of

opposite macros [2] were added to make it forward compatible. Those

are now [3] being removed.



Remove the fallback macros in the Chromium code so the code simply

refers to the enums defined in the header, instead of going through

two macros.



[1] https://crrev.com/c/3982602

[2] https://crrev.com/c/4167050/7/sys-kernel/linux-headers/files/0051-CHROMIUM-v4l2-add-upstream-work-in-progress-V4L2-AV1.patch#89

[3] https://crrev.com/c/4603378/1/sys-kernel/linux-headers/files/0051-FROMGIT-add-upstream-V4L2-AV1-stateless-controls.patch#b88

entry.title: Run the http cache lock in parallel with sending a request
entry.content:
This modifies the HTTP cache transaction state machine to race the cache

lock transaction against the sending of the network request (behind a

default-disabled feature flag). Unit tests and browser tests have been

updated to run with the feature enabled.



In the vast majority of cases, the cache lock will complete successfully

before the send completes.



In the rare case where the send completes before the cache lock is

acquired, the result of the send will be stored and used when the cache

lock completes.

entry.title: [dPWA] Support uninstallation of individual install URLs for externally managed web apps
entry.content:
There was no code path for removing an install URL from an externally

managed web app. Instead we were removing the associated install

source entirely. This CL fixes that behavior.



As part of this CL WebAppUninstallCommand is split up into three

different removal jobs:

- RemoveInstallUrlJob

- RemoveInstallSourceJob

- RemoveWebAppJob

Each job may invoke another one within the overall command's

AllAppsLock. These jobs basically make up an async function call

stack scoped within the lifetime of WebAppProvider.



https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4541923

attempted to do the same thing but was reverted due to crashes in

Lacros. I was not able to repro these crashes and it is my hope that

entry.title: Calculate minimum scroll delta to update intersection observation
entry.content:
During intersection update, IntersectionGeometry computes the

minimum distance that can change overlap relationship between the root

and the target in either direction, when it's applicable.

frame, and the accumulated scroll delta. On a scroll, the

LocalFrameView needs to update intersection only if the accumulated

scroll delta >= the minimum scroll delta to update.

entry.title: TooltipLacros: Reset tooltip before window is destructed
entry.content:
This CL calls HideAndReset() on OnWindowDestroying which runs before

window destruction instead of OnWindowDestroying which runs after.

HideAndReset() will call TooltipLacros::Hide() which refers to

`parent_window_` and it must be called before window is destructed.



This is a potential fix for TooltipLacros::Hide() crash on GetHost().

In the crash report, it hits to null `host_` inside `parent_window_`.

This is probably because window is destructed but `parent_window_` is

still not set to nullptr, and MouseEvent occurs between window

destruction somehow.

entry.title: Remove spurious visual data sync updates.
entry.content:
- Fix a spurious visual data sync update when dragging a group into a new window. We used to call OnGroupClosedInTabStrip followed by OnGroupOpenedInTabStrip, which meant we had to do an update of the visual data after re-opening it to get the header in the right state. Now, we just leave the connection intact the whole time, by going through the listener hierarchy and respecting pause state, so the header starts in the correct visual state in the new window.



- Fix a spurious visual data sync update when opening a saved group in the tabstrip. We used to create the local group, start listening to it, then update the visual data, creating a sync update; now we update the visual data before we start listening.

entry.title: [A11y] Remove subtrees of nodes removed from flat tree.
entry.content:
Create a method called RemoveSubtreeWhenSafe() that removes subtrees as

soon as it is safe to traverse the flat tree, so that there can be no

orphaned objects left in the cache.



Specifically, "when safe" means:

1) If CanSafelyUseFlatTraversal() returns true, do it now (flat

traversal is not forbidden and there are no pending slot assignments

2) Otherwise, do it towards the beginning of a11y's clean layout

processing. This may be later than necessary -- we may consider having

a special callback that occurs as soon as flat traversal is safe.
